ext\",\"text\":\"**Examining anonymous classes**\\n\\nIn version 1.4, the outer exception was identified as $11 from failures in loading. There are various nested actions tied to it, like a PrivilegedAction for `doPrivileged` and resource actions. In 1.5, I suspect that a user-generated file called `FormattersAnonymous12Anonymous2Test` is linked to a resource action identified as $12$2. The \\\"anonymous12\\\" might indicate a new overload. \\n\\nI need to check how these methods work, especially focusing on the indices for the new anonymous classes created in version 1.5 and their relation to resource handling.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Counting resource actions**\\n\\nI'm looking at a failing test, specifically regarding resource actions related to the classloader, which was previously noted as $11$3. I wonder if version 1.5 has an impact, possibly due to the absence of a SecurityManager. I need to count the nested elements in the 1.5 source code. The outer method `renderRaw` features `doPrivileged` with a new `PrivilegedAction<Void>` identified as $12$1. This could be important for understanding the changes in behavior.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_1MFLt2ki4tnsHyrQS1BVAyMD|fc_01da8a49d4971dc0016a23808784c881958bec543b7729b8d6", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); javac --release 8 -d \"$tmp\" $(find /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.5.3.Final/main/extracted -name '*.java') >/tmp/javac_jboss.out 2>&1; status=$?; echo status=$status tmp=$tmp; tail -50 /tmp/javac_jboss.out; if [ $status -eq 0 ]; then find \"$tmp/org/jboss/logmanager/formatters\" -name 'Formatters*.class' -printf '%f\n' | sort; fi", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 686, "output": 894, "cacheRead": 35840, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37420, "cost": {"input": 0, "output"